captions.text:
- I DON'T THINK IT HAS
TO BE HALLOWEEN TO SCARE PEOPLE.
I DO IT ALL YEAR LONG.

BACK TO SCHOOL,
RING THE BELL

CLIMB THE FENCE,
BOOKS AND PENS

I CAN TELL THAT WE ARE
GONNA BE FRIENDS

[singing]
- I CAN TELL THAT WE ARE

SO NOTHING WILL SCARE YOU
ANYMORE?

- AH!
- OH, MY GOD, OH, MY GOD!

- YOU WOULD NOT DRESS
AS A CLOWN.

- NO, I DON'T THINK
THERE'S ANYTHING--

I THINK--
THEY'RE JUST TOO SAD.

IT'S LIKE, "LOOK HOW HAPPY I AM,
BUT I'M NOT HAPPY AT ALL."

- DO THEY SCARE YOU?
- THEY SCARE THE HELL OUT OF ME.

Y'ALL WERE GREAT.
HAPPY HALLOWEEN, EVERYBODY.

BE KIND TO ONE ANOTHER.
BYE.
